parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent or Complete Failure of Rear Tail Lights and Brake Lights
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of rear tail lights and brake lights can cause a significant safety risk, as it may lead to accidents or collisions due to reduced visibility, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The rear tail lights and brake lights may not work at all
or they may work intermittently
causing confusion and uncertainty for other drivers on the road. The failure may occur suddenly
without warning
and may not trigger any warning messages on the vehicle's dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lights can increase the risk of a rear-end collision, which can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Brake lights do not illuminate when the brake pedal is depressed
brake lights flicker or work intermittently
brake lights stop working altogether.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power while driving, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Engine turns off while driving
loss of electrical power
difficulty shifting gears
vehicle hesitation or stalling
warning lights and messages on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear defroster and windshield can reduce visibility while driving, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Rear defroster emits smoke
overheats
or cracks the rear windshield
rear windshield cracks or shatters.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door lock actuator can make it difficult or impossible to lock or unlock the doors, which can increase the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Door locks do not work intermittently
door locks do not respond to the key fob
manual entry is not possible.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: OnStar/GPS Antenna Electrical Short and Corrosion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the OnStar/GPS antenna can cause electrical shorts and corrosion, which can increase the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: OnStar/GPS antenna electrical short
corrosion on the antenna cover
incorrect installation of the antenna cover.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power brake vacuum pump can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to a loss of braking power, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels hard or stiff
the brakes do not stop the vehicle
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle rolls or moves without stopping
the brake assist warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the trailer brake system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to a loss of braking power, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The "trailer brake system" warning message is displayed
the brakes do not stop the vehicle
the brake pedal feels hard or stiff
the vehicle rolls or moves without stopping.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lights can cause other drivers to not be aware of the vehicle's intention to stop, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake lights do not work
the brake lights work intermittently
the brake lights short out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake assist system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to a loss of braking power, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The "brake assist" warning message is displayed
the brakes do not stop the vehicle
the brake pedal feels hard or stiff
the vehicle rolls or moves without stopping.
